The paper discusses the integration of multimedia annotations and Linked Data principles, which are relevant to the Web and Information Retrieval (cs.WEB, cs.IR) fields. The Open Annotation Model is also discussed, which is a model for representing annotations on multimedia resources, relevant to Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Semantic Web (cs.SI) fields. Finally, the paper discusses the exchange of annotations via common Web standards, which is relevant to the Database (cs.DB) field.
